From the standard adiabatic boundary integration, work can be expressed as:
  $ W = (P_f V_f - P_i V_i) / (gamma - 1) = (P_i V_i) / (gamma - 1) [ (P_f V_f) / (P_i V_i) - 1 ] $
  
  Since the process is adiabatic, $P_i V_i^gamma = P_f V_f^gamma$, which means $P_f / P_i = (V_i / V_f)^gamma$. Substituting this pressure ratio into the bracketed statement yields:
  $ W = (P_i V_i) / (gamma - 1) [ (V_i / V_f)^gamma dot V_f / V_i - 1 ] = (P_i V_i) / (gamma - 1) [ (V_i / V_f)^(gamma - 1) - 1 ] $